High-level description For reliable autonomy under uncertainty, we must have efficient ways to estimate event likelihood given a stochastic system model.
Existing methods  Use sampling-based methods like Monte-Carlo simulation. Hoever, this approach only have asymptotic convergence guarantees. Compute the probability density via convolutions when the dynamics is linear. However, this iterative method requires gridding for numerical evalution of the convolution integral. Further, its accuracy degrades over long time horizons.
